  <para style="p">
    <verse number="15" style="v" sid="EST 4:15" />¶ Then <char style="w" strong="H0635">Esther</char> <char style="w" strong="H0559">bade</char> <char style="add">them</char> <char style="w" strong="H7725">return</char> <char style="w" strong="H4782">Mordecai</char> <char style="add">this answer</char>, <verse eid="EST 4:15" /><verse number="16" style="v" sid="EST 4:16" /><char style="w" strong="H3212">Go</char>, gather <char style="w" strong="H3664">together</char> all the <char style="w" strong="H3064">Jews</char> that are <char style="w" strong="H4672">present</char> in <char style="w" strong="H7800">Shushan</char>, and <char style="w" strong="H6684">fast</char> ye for me, and neither <char style="w" strong="H0398">eat</char> nor <char style="w" strong="H8354">drink</char> <char style="w" strong="H7969">three</char> <char style="w" strong="H3117">days</char>, <char style="w" strong="H3915">night</char> or <char style="w" strong="H3117">day</char>: I also and my <char style="w" strong="H5291">maidens</char> will <char style="w" strong="H6684">fast</char> likewise; and <char style="w" strong="H3651">so</char> will I <char style="w" strong="H0935">go</char> in unto the <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char>, which <char style="add">is</char> not according to the <char style="w" strong="H1881">law</char>: and if I <char style="w" strong="H0006">perish</char>, I <char style="w" strong="H0006">perish</char>.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">4.16 </char><char style="ft" closed="false">present: Heb. found</char></note> <verse eid="EST 4:16" /><verse number="17" style="v" sid="EST 4:17" />So <char style="w" strong="H4782">Mordecai</char> went his <char style="w" strong="H5674">way</char>, and <char style="w" strong="H6213">did</char> according to all that <char style="w" strong="H0635">Esther</char> had <char style="w" strong="H6680">commanded</char> him.<note caller="+" style="f"><char style="fr" closed="false">4.17 </char><char style="ft" cl