  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="EST 5:1" />Now it came to pass on the <char style="w" strong="H7992">third</char> <char style="w" strong="H3117">day</char>, that <char style="w" strong="H0635">Esther</char> put <char style="w" strong="H3847">on</char> <char style="add">her</char> <char style="w" strong="H4438">royal</char> <char style="add">apparel</char>, and <char style="w" strong="H5975">stood</char> in the <char style="w" strong="H6442">inner</char> <char style="w" strong="H2691">court</char> of the <char style="w" strong="H4428">king’s</char> <char style="w" strong="H1004">house</char>, over <char style="w" strong="H5227">against</char> the <char style="w" strong="H4428">king’s</char> <char style="w" strong="H1004">house</char>: and the <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char> <char style="w" strong="H3427">sat</char> upon his <char style="w" strong="H4438">royal</char> <char style="w" strong="H3678">throne</char> in the <char style="w" strong="H4438">royal</char> <char style="w" strong="H1004">house</char>, over <char style="w" strong="H5227">against</char> the <char style="w" strong="H6607">gate</char> of the <char style="w" strong="H1004">house</char>. <verse eid="EST 5:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="EST 5:2" />And it was so, when the <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char> <char style="w" strong="H7200">saw</char> <char style="w" strong="H0635">Esther</char> the <char style="w" strong="H4436">queen</char> <char style="w" strong="H5975">standing</char> in the <char style="w" strong="H2691">court</char>, <char style="add">that</char> she <char style="w" strong="H5375">obtained</char> <char style="w" strong="H2580">favour</char> in his <char style="w" strong="H5869">sight</char>: and the <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char> held <char style="w" strong="H3447">out</char> to <char style="w" strong="H0635">Esther</char> the <char style="w" strong="H2091">golden</char> <char style="w" strong="H8275">sceptre</char> that <char style="add">was<