  <para style="p">
    <verse number="1" style="v" sid="EST 9:1" />Now in the <char style="w" strong="H8147">twelfth</char> <char style="w" strong="H2320">month</char>, that <char style="add">is</char>, the <char style="w" strong="H2320">month</char> <char style="w" strong="H0143">Adar</char>, on the <char style="w" strong="H7969">thirteenth</char> <char style="w" strong="H3117">day</char> of the same, when the <char style="w" strong="H4428">king’s</char> <char style="w" strong="H1697">commandment</char> and his <char style="w" strong="H1881">decree</char> drew <char style="w" strong="H5060">near</char> to be put in <char style="w" strong="H6213">execution</char>, in the <char style="w" strong="H3117">day</char> that the <char style="w" strong="H0341">enemies</char> of the <char style="w" strong="H3064">Jews</char> <char style="w" strong="H7663">hoped</char> to have <char style="w" strong="H7980">power</char> over them, (though it was <char style="w" strong="H2015">turned</char> to the contrary, that the <char style="w" strong="H3064">Jews</char> had <char style="w" strong="H7980">rule</char> over them that <char style="w" strong="H8130">hated</char> them;) <verse eid="EST 9:1" /><verse number="2" style="v" sid="EST 9:2" />The <char style="w" strong="H3064">Jews</char> gathered themselves <char style="w" strong="H6950">together</char> in their <char style="w" strong="H5892">cities</char> throughout all the <char style="w" strong="H4082">provinces</char> of the <char style="w" strong="H4428">king</char> <char style="w" strong="H0325">Ahasuerus</char>, to <char style="w" strong="H7971">lay</char> <char style="w" strong="H3027">hand</char> on such as <char style="w" strong="H1245">sought</char> their <char style="w" strong="H7451">hurt</char>: and no <char style="w" strong="H0376">man</char> could <char style="w" strong="H5975">withstand</char> <char style="w" strong="H6440">them</char>; for the <char style="w" strong="H6343">fear</char> of them <char style="w" strong="H5307">fell</char>